## Patterns to follow (and the file that owns each)

### Adding a tool
- Handler: `apps/web/src/lib/agent/tools/handlers/<slug>.ts` (or extend the
  bridge in `tools/handlers.ts`).
- Citation extractor: `apps/web/src/lib/agent/citations.ts`.
- Registry seed: `scripts/seed-tools.ts`.
- Eval case: `apps/web/src/evals/goldens.ts`.

### Adding a workflow
- Implementation: `apps/web/src/lib/workflows/<name>.ts` with `enqueueX`
  and `runX`.
- Dispatcher: `apps/web/src/app/api/cron/workflows/route.ts` switch.
- Schedule (only if new): `vercel.json` cron + `cron/learning` enqueue.

### Adding a webhook
- Route: `apps/web/src/app/api/webhooks/<source>/route.ts`.
- HMAC verification mandatory (see `webhooks/transcripts/route.ts` for
  pattern). Idempotency key in `webhook_deliveries`.

### Adding an ontology object type
- TypeScript: `packages/core/src/types/ontology.ts`.
- Zod schema: `packages/core/src/types/schemas.ts`.
- URN helper: `packages/core/src/types/urn.ts`.
- Migration: new file `packages/db/migrations/NNN_*.sql` with RLS.

### Telemetry
Every meaningful event flows through `emitAgentEvent` / `emitOutcomeEvent`
from `@prospector/core/telemetry`. The agent route emits at every step.
Webhooks emit `outcome_events`. Action panel emits `action_invoked`.
Without these the learning loop has nothing to learn from.

## Common mistakes (do NOT)

- DO NOT hardcode business context — always read from `business_profiles`.
- DO NOT hardcode tool definitions — always load from `tool_registry` via
  the tool-loader. The static factory is fallback only.
- DO NOT clone agents per rep — one template with dynamic context per role.
- DO NOT skip `tenant_id` scoping in Supabase queries.
- DO NOT compute funnel benchmarks in real-time — they're weekly batch.
- DO NOT send alerts without cooldown — `SlackDispatcher` accepts a
  `CooldownStore`, use `SupabaseCooldownStore` in production.
- DO NOT skip citations — every tool result must produce citations via the
  extractor in `agent/citations.ts`.
- DO NOT skip the feedback loop — thumbs up/down + action invocations
  must persist; without them, the bandit + prompt optimizer have no signal.
- DO NOT ship demo data in analytics — empty states beat fake numbers.
- DO NOT ship a new "agent type" — surfaces are presets of the one universal
 agent. New capability = new tool, new context strategy, or a new surface
 preset (which is just a prompt + tool subset). Never a new runtime.
- DO NOT bypass the holdout cohort — `shouldSuppressPush` from
  `lib/workflows/holdout.ts` runs on every proactive push.
- DO NOT assume Indeed Flex context — the system is multi-tenant by design.

## When in doubt

Read [`MISSION.md`](MISSION.md). If the change you're considering doesn't
advance one of the two jobs (build pipeline / manage existing customers),
or violates a UX principle, push back.
